They call Paris the City of Lights for a reason. Imagine, walking amongst historical buildings, down a quaint street. Upon turning the corner, there she is: the Eiffel Tower. It's evening, the city cloaked in darkness, but all of a sudden, the Eiffel Tower is sparkling, quite literally. 

I absolutely love Paris and the romance that it brings. During my recent visit, it dawned on me that the beauty of Paris is finding beauty in the smallest of moments. There is no rush and no stress. It's just Parisians enjoying time with their family and friends. Sitting at quaint cafes, a glass of wine in hand while they watch the world pass them by. I learned that enjoying the quiet moments of life are what make life so beautiful. ", "document_id": null}]}

